I&#39;m no Firebase expert.

But instead of direct Http requests I would rather use the dedicated [Firebase Unity SDK](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/unity/start)and then you can simply follow the manual for [Retrieving Data](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/unity/retrieve-data) and [Save Data](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/unity/save-data). I would assume you are using a &quot;Realtime Database&quot; for now.

First you always need to initialize your reference 

    public class FirebaseController : MonoBehaviour 
    {
        DatabaseReference reference

        private void Start() 
        {
            
            // Set these values before calling into the realtime database.
            FirebaseApp.DefaultInstance.SetEditorDatabaseUrl(&quot;https://YOUR-FIREBASE-APP.firebaseio.com/&quot;);

            // If usig restricted access then also do
            //FirebaseApp.DefaultInstance.SetEditorP12FileName(&quot;YOUR-FIREBASE-APP-P12.p12&quot;);
            //FirebaseApp.DefaultInstance.SetEditorServiceAccountEmail(&quot;SERVICE-ACCOUNT-ID@YOUR-FIREBASE-APP.iam.gserviceaccount.com&quot;);
            //FirebaseApp.DefaultInstance.SetEditorP12Password(&quot;notasecret&quot;);

            // Get the root reference location of the database.
            DatabaseReference reference = FirebaseDatabase.DefaultInstance.RootReference;
        }

        ...
    }

### Save data 

1. If using JSON you need the according structure for your data as c# classes. Since I don&#39;t know your data structure I will just go with the examples from the Firebase manual here

        // I would always make these classes serializable so you can directly 
        // also see, edit and save them via the Inspector
        [Serializable]
        public class User 
        {
            public string username;
            public string email;
        
            public User() 
            {
            }
        
            public User(string username, string email) 
            {
                this.username = username;
                this.email = email;
            }
        }

   Then you can save the data as json like

        private void writeNewUser(string userId, string name, string email) 
        {
            User user = new User(name, email);
            string json = JsonUtility.ToJson(user);
        
            reference.Child(&quot;users&quot;).Child(userId).SetRawJsonValueAsync(json);
        }

2. Or instead use the full path in the firebase structure to only set a single value without the need for a JSON and according class in c# using 

         reference.Child(&quot;users&quot;).Child(userId).Child(&quot;username&quot;).SetValueAsync(name);

### Retrieving Data

For retrieving you do the same

    reference.Child(&quot;users&quot;).GetValueAsync().ContinueWith(task =&gt; 
    {
        if (task.IsFaulted) 
        {
            // Handle the error...
        }
        else if (task.IsCompleted) 
        {
            DataSnapshot snapshot = task.Result;
            // Do something with snapshot...
            
            // Again either using a JSON
            var user = JsonUtility.FromJson&lt;User&gt;(snapshot.Child(userId).GetRawJsonValue());
            var username = user.username;

            // OR using the path to get a single value
            var username = (string)snapshot.Child(userId).Child(&quot;username&quot;).Value();


            // Now do something with the received data
        }
    });

**Note**: As I have seen it quite often here on SO there is also a little issue with [threading](https://firebase.googleblog.com/2019/07/firebase-and-tasks-how-to-deal-with.html) and `ContinueWith` end on a thread where you can&#39;t call any Unity API. So you should probably rather go for [`ContinueWithOnMainThread`](https://firebase.google.com/docs/reference/unity/class/firebase/extensions/task-extension) instead

---

*As said I&#39;m no firebase expert and only trying to understand and provide an example following the linked guides ... no warranty that this is how these methods really work ;)*

